# Nestar-Style Architecture Guide for This Project

This project follows a **simplified version** of the Nestar client architecture you described, adapted for **Next.js + Tailwind + Apollo Client** and the existing folder names in this repo. Labels, existing names, and current APIs are **not** changed; this rule guides *structure and organization only*.

## 1. Component Structure & Order

All React components (pages and `libs/components/*`) should keep this **section ordering**:

```tsx
// 1) IMPORTS (grouped & ordered)
// - React / Next core
// - External libs (icons, etc.)
// - Internal hooks
// - Apollo (queries/mutations)
// - Types & enums
// - Utils/helpers
// - Config/constants

// 2) PROPS INTERFACES / TYPES (if needed)

// 3) COMPONENT FUNCTION
// 4) HOOKS & LOCAL STATE (useState, useEffect, useMemo, useCallback)
// 5) APOLLO REQUESTS (useQuery, useMutation) grouped together
// 6) LIFECYCLES (useEffect hooks) grouped under a comment
// 7) HANDLERS (event & business logic)
// 8) CONDITIONAL RENDERING (early returns for loading/error/mobile)
// 9) MAIN JSX RETURN (desktop/default layout)
// 10) DEFAULT PROPS (only if truly needed)
```

Use comments to keep this consistent:

```tsx
/** APOLLO REQUESTS **/
/** LIFECYCLES **/
/** HANDLERS **/
```

## 2. Handlers Pattern

- **Event handlers**: `handle*` (e.g. `handleOpenFilters`, `handleChangeSearch`).
- **Business logic handlers**: `*Handler` (e.g. `createQuoteHandler`, `saveOrganizationHandler`).
- **Input handlers**: `handle*Change` or `getInput*Handler` (consistent per file).
- Put **component-specific handlers inside the component**.
- If a handler is reused across multiple components, move it to:
  - `libs/utils.ts` or
  - a more specific util file in `libs/utils/`.
- All async handlers use `try/catch` and user-safe logging / toasts (this project may not use sweetAlert; reuse existing notification pattern instead of adding new ones).

## 3. GraphQL Queries & Mutations

- Keep the existing split:
  - `apollo/user/query.ts`
  - `apollo/user/mutation.ts`
  - `apollo/admin/*` for admin-only operations
- Group queries/mutations by **domain** using comment blocks:

```ts
// ============================================
// PROVIDER QUERIES
// ============================================
```

- Naming:
  - Queries: `GET_*` (e.g. `GET_PROVIDER_ORGANIZATION`, `GET_SERVICE_REQUESTS`).
  - Mutations: imperative verbs (e.g. `CREATE_*`, `UPDATE_*`, `CHANGE_*`).
- Always request only the fields needed by the UI; when adding new UI fields (rating, budgets, images), extend the existing query blocks rather than creating new ones.

## 4. Hooks

- Custom hooks live in `lib/hooks/` or `libs/hooks/` (reuse existing structure).
- Naming: always `useSomething`, typed returns.
- Hooks wrap:
  - Apollo calls + mapping logic, or
  - shared stateful behaviors (device detection, profile organization, etc.).
- Components should prefer using hooks like `useProviderOrganization` instead of duplicating query + mapping logic.

## 5. Types & Enums

- Types for providers/organizations and related entities live in `libs/types/`.
- Enums live in `libs/enums/`.
- General rules:
  - Interfaces & types: PascalCase (`Provider`, `ProviderOrganizationInput`).
  - Enum names: PascalCase (`OrganizationStatus`), values: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`.
- When updating GraphQL fields (e.g. adding rating or budgets), also align the corresponding TypeScript types so components don’t fall back to `any`.

## 6. Layout & Pages

- Pages under `pages/` are thin:
  - Import the main layout and high-level components from `libs/components/*`.
  - Handle only routing, top-level layout selection, and simple prop wiring.
- Shared layout elements:
  - `Navbar`, `Footer`, dashboard headers/sidebars live in `libs/components/`.
  - Keep them stateless where possible; stateful behavior in hooks or container components.

## 7. Tailwind & Styling

- Tailwind is the primary styling system.
- Avoid introducing new SCSS; prefer Tailwind utility classes and existing design tokens.
- When refactoring old SCSS-based components, keep layout & semantics but move styles into Tailwind classes gradually; do not mix many styling systems in the same new code.

## 8. Code Organization & Cleanliness

- **Do not change existing public names / labels / routes** unless explicitly required by the feature. Adapt structure only.
- Prefer:
  - Smaller, focused components over monolithic ones.
  - Extracting repeated chunks (cards, rows) into `libs/components/` subcomponents.
  - Moving low-level data transformation into `libs/utils/providerMapper.ts` or similar mappers.
- Remove or avoid:
  - New sprawling Markdown docs in the repo (we use this `.mdc` for architecture).
  - Duplicated queries/mutations.
  - Unused components or dead code when you are sure nothing imports them.

## 9. Data Flow

Follow this general pattern for UI → GraphQL → UI round trips:

1. **Component** calls a handler (e.g. `handleSaveOrganization`).
2. Handler invokes a **mutation** from `apollo/user/mutation.ts`.
3. Use `refetch` or `refetchQueries` from the relevant `useQuery` to refresh data.
4. Map backend data through mappers in `libs/utils/*` (e.g. `providerMapper`) into the internal `Provider` shape.
5. React components render only this mapped shape.

This keeps:
- Components focused on rendering and interaction,
- Mappers focused on field name differences between backend and frontend,
- GraphQL files focused on transport.

